summary: Jannik Sinner made a successful return to the US Open after avoiding a ban related to a doping case. Candidates in Canal Flats, British Columbia, are actively campaigning. name: Rugby
summary: International rugby news highlights the upcoming events and achievements in the sport. The Canadian Men's Rugby team faced a loss against Japan in the Pacific Nations Cup, while the Women's team has finalized its recruiting class for 2024. The USA and Canada will compete in the PNC 2024, featuring wheelchair rugby, also known as "murderball," a demanding sport that requires immense skill and determination. Aurélie Rivard made her #Paris2024 debut, and Canada and the USA faced off in wheelchair rugby, with Sarah Adam becoming the first woman on the U.S. wheelchair rugby team. The Major League Rugby College Draft announced its results for 2024, and UBC and Victoria emerged as top teams in the coaches' poll. Great Britain faces a challenge in defending its wheelchair rugby crown at Paris 2024, while Canada is expected to compete for a medal in the same event at the Paralympic Games.

summary: In a stunning upset at the 2024 US Open, defending champion Novak Djokovic was defeated in the third round by Australian Alexei Popyrin. The 28th-seeded Popyrin, who had never faced Djokovic before, pulled off the surprising victory despite Djokovic's strong performance this season. Popyrin himself acknowledged that he had believed he could win, and the victory has given him confidence and excitement for the rest of the tournament. Djokovic's loss eliminated another top seed from the US Open, adding to the growing list of upsets that have occurred during the 2024 Grand Slam.

summary: The All Blacks of New Zealand faced off against the Springboks of South Africa in a thrilling Rugby Championship match. The Springboks emerged victorious with a 31-27 score, making it their third consecutive win over the All Blacks. The match was a close affair, with the All Blacks leading briefly in the first half before the Springboks rallied to take the lead. The match showcased the resilience of the Springboks, who fought back from a 20-17 deficit in the second half. The match was also notable for the debut of young Springboks prodigy Jaden Hendrikse, who impressed with his performance. The media hailed the Springboks' victory and praised the team's "brilliance" and the impact of their "Bomb Squad" strategy.

name: Shaun Johnson
summary: In a remarkable farewell, retiring NRL star Shaun Johnson orchestrated a stunning upset for the New Zealand Warriors in their victory over the Cronulla Sharks. Despite a "dreadful" act that sparked uproar, Johnson's "miracle" try assist in the final seconds secured the Warriors' triumph. The match was marred by a sin bin penalty against the Sharks, which proved costly, as Johnson led the Warriors' comeback. Johnson's performance left fans stunned and earned him a match-winning farewell, saving his "party trick" for the end of his illustrious career. Following his retirement, Johnson expressed his gratitude for his support, paying tribute to his late coach Andrew Webster. Despite his retirement, Johnson remains ready to explore opportunities with Fox, demonstrating his quick wit and eagerness to continue making an impact on the game.
